    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-15T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="440"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0051/250: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="from"
                            >Cole</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-15T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 15, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 16—8:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. From Murphy. Your 160 [<hi rend="italic">222</hi>], November 12, 5 p.m., via
                    Tangier. All consular officers in North Africa are being instructed as requested
                    to maintain appropriate contacts with local officials as heretofore. They are
                    extending full cooperation to our military authorities.</p>
                <p>As the Department is undoubtedly aware my designation as personal representative
                    of the President under his directive of September 22<note n="68"
                        xml:id="d440fn68">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_379">p. 379</ref>.</note>
                    ceased with the arrival of our armed forces and I am now acting under the same
                    directive as “Civil Affairs Officer of Allied Forces”. [Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
